content.description: Has a PG rating in Austin Climbing for "bolt 3 is somewhat runout but on easy moves"

To the right of the roof capped dihedral that marks the end of Mossy Wall and the beginning of Middle Earth Wall.  Easy 5.9ish climbing up big holds over the mud ledge to a difficult behind your head clip and some delicate long moves over the bulge  Distinguishable by the blank scooping bulge at the top.
content.location: first route from the left.  Starts just right of the larger block that froms the corridor to Mossy Wall.

content.description: Climb to first high bolt on easy climbing. Route heads to the right after 3rd bolt.
content.location: Between Elvin Beauty and Blood of Dwarves.

content.description: Starts a few feet right of the first bolt with a high right foot on the obvious point/edge. Follow up the right side of the bolts, using the left edge of the huge huecos if you want. Alternatively, follow the bolt line straight up on thin edges, crimps, and craters. Feels a little easier than the grade with the huecos, and a little harder following the bolt line directly.
content.location: Second bolted line to the left of the obvious chimney - in between Orcs Drool to the left and My Precious to the right.

content.description: Has a R rating in the Austin Climbing book for "bolt 3 being runout on hard moves"
Solid holds, most are thin and sharp, great friction. Two great underclings(occupied by daddy longlegs), one at the at the beginning and the other a few moves later.
content.location: A little over 5 minute walk from north shore parking lot. The route is on the Middle Earth Wall, to the Right of the boulder. if you have the "Austin Climbing" by hogges Guide book it's in between "Orcs Drool" and "My Precious".

content.description: Climb two black tufas, then thru the roof.  This route gets an 'R' rating because a fall before clipping the 3rd bolt could result in hitting the boulder at the base.  Belayer must be attentive to avoid letting that happen.
content.location: Right of Mines of Moria route. There is a long 5-foot tall boulder at the base, with a sharp edge.

content.description: Climbs to the right of the water streak. It's anchors are on the right side of the roofs. Last bolt to anchors is slightly run out, be careful.
content.location: Between Dwarves Rule and My Precious near Moria Cave.

climbs.name: One Ring to Rule Them All

content.description: All bolts are run out. If your not comfortable leading 5.8...this route could be realy dicey. Any falls would result in pain, if not injury.
content.location: Downhill from the furthest left routes. The route starts on a downhill landing.

content.description: Shares TR anchors with Halfling's Leaf.    Start just inside the cave. face out and work the right arÃªte around onto the right face
Nice climb to set up a top rope for Middle Earth Cave

Start to the right of the giant chimney crack that makes up "Hello World".  Climb through easy moves on big holds to the roof at the top.  Large holds and fun footwork at the top make for some fun thuggish moves to the chains
content.location: Right of the obvious chimney crack

content.description: Cool looking chimney-tube formation
Fun warm up on easy climbing. Big holds all the way up. Angle gets lower as you climb up.
content.location: Between Blood of Dwarves and Fallohide. The ledge below has half-round tube indention.

content.description: Starts and climbs Hello World left of Moria Cave. However, this route is an extension. When you get to the first anchors, continue up on one more bolt above the small roof. To minimize rope drag, bring a long draw or runner to help reduce drag. A second set of anchors are above the last bolt. Crux is definitely pulling the roof...but makes the route so much better.
content.location: Left of Moria Cave. Same roue as Hello Word, just extend the route by going over small roof.

content.description: Climbs left of the Moria Cave. One has been known to use the opposing wall to chimney start this route.
content.location: The line that is directly left of the Moria Cave.

content.description: Climb bolt line up the thin crack.  First bolt is between the two horizontal and very wide cracks lower on the wall.  Route is almost vertical.
content.location: First route right of narrow and very tall cave with old dead tree in it.

content.description: Cool featured route, down low have sweet mini tufa holds, climb to dirty ledge. Pull jugs to get on wall. Good face climb with great holds.
content.location: Route is  above the boulders, between Troll Teeth and Bilbo's Bag.

content.description: Left of Troll Teeth. First route on the big open book dihedral on the Middle Earth Wall.
content.location: Located on the open book dihedral. First route on Middle Earth Wall.

content.description: Fun climbing up big holds. There is a feature to the right of the route that looks like someone took a giant core sample out of the wall. That can be used for interesting holds.
Nice route. Crux is right before the top. You just have to look for the holds. Might not be noticeable off the bat.
content.location: 3 routes to the right of Troll Teeth

content.description: Starts at the very end near Wall of Insanity.  Easy climbing up to the third bolt where you can sit on the ledge to rest before pulling a crux move over the roof.  Runs out on easy climbing until the 4th bolt before clipping anchor.
content.location: Middle Earth Wall.  Walk pass the big splitting crack about 10 feet and look for a small roof pull over a huge standing ledge.

content.description: As most of the routes in this section of middle earth, pull up to the wall from the ledge below. First three bolts are close to protect from decking on boulder below. Slight runout to bolt 4 and then 5. If you don't have a good belay, if you take a fall on 4, can possibly deck on boulder below. Crux is near bolt 4, and then you have to pull the small roof to reach anchors. Climbs the left side of the water streak.
content.location: It's behind the big 20' wide boulder left of Orc's drool. Line is next to water streak.

content.description: Start Mines of Moria which is to the right of Moria Cave, at bolt three, start traversing over to Ringbearer 5th bolt which is a permadraw, and continue right towards Dwarves Rule 5th bolt which is located on small roof, pull the roof and finish on Dwarves Rule's anchors. This is a variation route of the Mines of Moria.
content.protection: 5 bolts to anchors. After bolt 4, traverse to bolt 5 is runout and there is potential for an ugly swing.
content.location: Same start as Mines of Moria route.

content.description: Start on ledge with some pretty cool formations. May share climbing space with Tookish.
content.protection: 4 bolts to anchors. Avoid having two climbers climb simul on Tookish or Blood of Dwarves.
content.location: Between Tookish and Hobbit Hole.

content.description:
A bunchy of good pockets lead up to a small roof. Get over that and your at the chains.  

  Found in between The Fellowship and Elvin Beauty. Bolt 1 is pretty high up there and you have to pull on some pretty lousy holds to get up to it.
content.location: Found in between the Fellowship and Elvin Beauty.

content.description: Nice warmup route if you're in the area. Crux is the start.
content.location: 2 routes to the left of the large vertical cave.

content.description: Another good warmup route if you're in the area. Crux def the start and can be right before the anchors if you don't see the holds. Might be a little problematic if you're not at least a solid high 10 climber.
content.location: Just to the left of the large vertical cave.

content.description: Morning shade.  Home to many easy and moderate routes. At least here the mud-ledge is less muddy and pronounced.  The wall can be distinguished by the large chimney that makes up "Hello World" to the right and the far left dihedral that is capped by a small roof.  This dihedral is considered part of Mossy Wall, which is around the left corner.  Routes on the far left dihedral start in a corridor between the wall and a giant block (some start on top of the block)
